==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin [[editor#Latin|editor]] ‘producer, displayer’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈɛdɪtə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|editors}}

# A person who [[edits]] or makes changes to documents, or who has edited a particular document.
#: ''John Johnson wrote this term paper and the '''editor''' was Joan Johnson.''
# A person at a newspaper or similar institution who edits stories and decides which ones to publish.
#: ''John is the city '''editor''' at the ''Daily Times''.''
# {{cattag|computer software}} A program for creating and making changes to text files and documents.
#: ''The TPU EVE '''editor''' is an excellent, extensible, programmable editor.''

